================================================================================
                         PACKAGING GUIDELINES
================================================================================

For Downstream Packagers (Linux Distros, etc.):

1. Include NOTICE with distribution
   - Reference this file in package metadata (README, spec file, etc.)
   
2. Verify GPL-2.0 Compliance
   - All third-party deps listed here are GPL-compatible
   - No GPL-3.0 obligations triggered
   - If modified, comply with GPL-2.0 source disclosure requirements
   
3. Link SDL2 Dynamically
   - SDL2 is typically system-provided (libsdl2-2.30+)
   - Do not statically link if possible (reduces package size)
   - SDL2_mixer is optional (audio playback is a future roadmap item)
   
4. Python Dependencies
   - Build-time only; not distributed in binary packages
   - Asset/audio generation tools can be packaged separately
   - See tools/README.md for asset pipeline details
   
5. License Attribution
   - Include LICENSE (GPL-2.0 header)
   - Include this NOTICE file
   - Optional: Include SDL2-2.30.9/LICENSE.txt for SDL2 license copy

